title: Shares of some technology companies are trading higher on continued optimism amid the reopening of the economy, which would increase consumer spending and economic activity.

Shares of several technology companies are trading higher as equities continue to gain on optimism over an economic reopening as well as a smaller-than-expected drop in nonfarm payrolls. The sector has performed well this year amid the stay-at-home environment, which has been a positive for virtual communication, enterprise software and e-commerce.
